"n.阶层；等级制度 【英】 n. 阶层；等级制度(a system of ranks) 【记】 hier(神圣)+archy(统 治)→僧侣统治→等级 制度 【同】 同根词：hieratic(僧 侣的); hieron(圣地) n. 阶层; 等级制度 【记】原指: 希腊神话中天使的级别或等级hier神圣的, archy统治－神圣的统治－阶层; 等级制度 【参】hieratic(adj 僧侣的); hieron(n 神庙; 圣地) 【类】echelon: hierarchy 梯队: 层次 【记】hier 神圣+ archy 统治→僧侣统治→等级制 hierarchy (n.)  mid-14c., from Old French ierarchie, from Medieval Latin hierarchia ""ranked division of angels"" (in the system of Dionysius the Areopagite), from Greek hierarkhia ""rule of a high priest,"" from hierarkhes ""high priest, leader of sacred rites,"" from ta hiera ""the sacred rites"" (neuter plural of hieros ""sacred;"" see ire) + arkhein ""to lead, rule"" (see archon). Sense of ""ranked organization of persons or things"" first recorded 1610s, initially of clergy, sense probably influenced by higher. Related: Hierarchal; hierarchical."
